column5: it's made by the same people that made the hair gel in the movie "something about Mary".....       LOL just kidding   don't need the gloves, my wife bought me some manly purple gloves.........but thanks
HAHAHA. Too funny.
LOL that's the one  I can't remember the name of it it has a familiar scent
Rice lake??
That would be better than returning from a guided tour by the Steelyourstuffcre.com guys!

I woke up and saw the wind was down and it wasn't raining so I hooked up the boat and went to a secret local lake. I can't say the name but I heard " it has more people fishing it every year, than all people fishing all the lakes in Manitoba " I fished for bass and caught bass  I fished for perch and caught lots of perch  I fished for pike.........did I mention I caught lots of perch   the bass were biting pretty well as long as you cranked slowly, I guess I shouldn't say what lure I was using I heard some people don't like too much info given     tons of perch on secret baits      the average size was about the one in this picture but I can't say just how big they were      I guess I shouldn't say how deep I was fishing but I can say that my HDS5 was working well       it was a nice day on the water             there was a memorial of the guy guy that drowned recently, it made it very difficult to launch the boat by myself, but got it done with out disturbing the items left by friends  when I came back in someone was arranging the flowers and taking care of all the items, then 2 more came to pay their respects I guess it's a good way to let the family know he was loved
Nice report Terry. The momorial was a nice touch.
Nice report Terry !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  but you forgot to block out the back ground on the pictures...
Sounds like you had a good time Terry Memorial at the end was a definite nice touch as DanC mentioned Nice bass & perch Leechman
thanks for reminding me OH yeah I had to blank most of the photo out because it showed too much but enjoy it anyways
When you going to take up hunting?  Nice report bud.

you mean get back into hunting...I tried to renew my outdoor hunting and fishing card/ license for next year on-line but it would not let me, guess I have to wait till closer to next year.........  and I find it hard to find the time to fish when would I ever find the time to hunt too
Simple.... kill two birds with one stone..... scuba dive
Fishing is sooooo over rated these days.Work all summer,then sit in a tree all fall.
Good report. It was a great day to be on the water. I worked instead though
why bother posting if your not sharing any info
Thanks for the report Terry, I needed a good laugh     Well, except for the memorial shot, that is sad  Joey
Great report Terry.  Good to see you got out.

Looks like a good perch lake! I need to find a awesome perch lake around here... I'm trying to find some good ones for winter fishing in the last couple of years but "perch lakes" like i mean nice perch are hard to find around here !
Looks like a great day out on the water  Too bad you couldn't tell us about it.

It really bothers me when people don't tell you what's working on their secret Lake, now I won't know what to use when I figure out where you were Great Report & a nice memorial Thanx for posting Richard
hmm...sounds like adverstising to me. What r u trying to sell here?  sounds like a good time on the water. Cheers
well I am starting a guide/car detailing service I take you out for a day of fishing and by the time we return my helpers have wax and detailed you car
Thanks for the chuckle Terry !!!  ..we're off and I'll yak with you thru the week.

congrats terry next time how about a gps number then all the blanks would be filled in
Terry!  Any chance the HDS5 shot can be moved a little to the left to show the whole unit?  Nice lookin machine!

I don't usually ask this Terry, becuase I know people are very protective of their spots and techniques, but could you please tell me what you were using and the lake you were on?  Please feel free to PM me.  Thanks.

I don't think it would be right to say I was on simcoe and I wouldn't even consider telling people I used a 2.5" gulp minnow on a 1/4" jig and the rapala DT for bass.........  so I will not PM you with the info
